The paper discusses methods for aligning distributions, which is a common problem in machine learning. The use of adversarial distance and gradient descent optimization suggests that the paper belongs to the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also applies the method to image domain adaptation, which falls under "Computer Vision" (cs.CV). The use of discriminators and dual formulations suggests a connection to "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses stability and convergence, which is related to "Systems and Control" (cs.SY).
